The notice shall:
Be published once in a newspaper of general circulation in the county where the statutory trustâ€™s principal office, or, if none in this Commonwealth, its registered office, is or was last located;
Provide the name of the statutory trust and, if a series statutory trust, the name or names under which each series has transacted business;
Describe the information that must be included in a claim and provide a mailing address where the claim may be sent; and
State that a claim against the trust, or in the case of a series trust a claim against a series or against the property of or associated with a series, will be barred unless a proceeding to enforce the claim is commenced within two (2) years after the publication of the notice.
